This pin (REL1_43) IS the fidelity guarantee: mw.html / mw.text / mw.uri behave
as they do on a wiki running that MediaWiki release. To track a different
release, re-vendor the lualib from that branch and update this file.

Headless-init status (src/mwenv.lua wires each via setupInterface with a
minimal/empty mw_interface stand-in — see the per-lib comments there):
  mw.text     FULLY HEADLESS (lualib)  — trim/encode/decode/split; the PHP-only
                                         paths (unstrip/killMarkers/json*) are
                                         stubbed and error only if hit
  mw.uri      FULLY HEADLESS (lualib)  — encode/decode pure-Lua; focused shim
                                         installed if init throws
  mw.html     FULLY HEADLESS (lualib)  — self-contained builder, uniq markers only

SHIMMED in src/mwenv.lua (the full libs need deep PHP locale/parser callbacks;
only the format-facing surface module code uses is shimmed):
  mw.ustring  — byte-wise via Lua string.* PLUS a real UTF-8 char/codepoint
                (mw.text.decode needs char to expand numeric entities). Not the
                full ~15k-line Unicode lib; re-vendor it from REL1_43 if a suite
                needs real multibyte case/normalisation.
  mw.language — grouped formatNum (U+2212 minus, as on-wiki) + lc/uc/ucfirst/lcfirst
  mw.title    — benign stub object (getCurrentTitle / makeTitle / new)
  mw.site     — File namespace (id 6); consumers can override via config setup
  mw.getCurrentFrame / mw.log / mw.dumpObject — minimal core

NOT provided here: consumer-specific surface (mw.ext.*, render-primitive stubs).
The consumer supplies those through scribuntounit.config.lua (stubs + setup hook).
